# API Route Contracts

- Validate request shape at route boundaries before business logic executes.
- Return stable, explicit JSON response shapes for success and failure paths.
- Never leak credentials, tokens, stack traces, or provider internals in API responses.
- Enforce agency/project ownership checks before returning project or deliverable data.
- Keep API handlers thin; delegate domain logic to `lib/*` modules.
